Single File Programming Question
Plan Course Completion Order



A university in Chennai offers n courses labeled from 0 to n-1. Some courses have prerequisites.



For example:



[1, 0] → To take course 1, you must first complete course 0



You must determine a valid order to complete all courses.



If possible → print one valid order
If not possible (cycle exists) → print -1
Input format :
First line: integer n → number of courses
Second line: integer m → number of prerequisite pairs
Next m lines: two integers a b
meaning: b → a (b must be done before a)

Output format :
Print course order (space-separated)
If impossible → print -1
Code constraints :
1 <= n <= 2000
0 <= m <= 5000
No duplicate edges
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
4
4
1 0
2 0
3 1
3 2
Output 1 :
0 1 2 3
Input 2 :
2
1
1 0
Output 2 :
0 1
Note :
The program will be evaluated only after the “Submit Code” is clicked.
Extra spaces and new line characters in the program output will result in the failure of the test case.

*************************************
SOLUTION
*************************************

🔹 Core Idea (What this problem is)
This is a Topological Sorting problem on a Directed Graph
Courses = nodes
Prerequisites = directed edges (b → a)
🔹 Key Observation
You can only take a course when its dependencies are finished
So:
Course with no prerequisites → start first
Then remove it and update others
🔹 Approach (Step-by-step thinking)
1. Build Graph
Create adjacency list
For every pair [a, b]:
Add edge b → a

👉 Means: after finishing b, you can go to a

2. Track Dependencies
Use indegree[]
indegree[i] = number of prerequisites of course i
3. Start with Independent Courses
Add all nodes with indegree = 0 into queue

👉 These are courses you can take immediately

4. Process (BFS / Kahn’s Algorithm)

While queue not empty:

Take one course
Add it to result
For all its neighbors:
Reduce their indegree
If indegree becomes 0 → add to queue
5. Detect Cycle
If you processed all n courses → valid order
If not → cycle exists → return -1

*************************************
CODE
*************************************
import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int m = sc.nextInt();
        ArrayList<ArrayList<Integer>> adj = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            adj.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }
        
        int[] indegree = new int[n];
        
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            int a = sc.nextInt();
            int b = sc.nextInt();
            adj.get(b).add(a);
            indegree[a]++;
        }
        
        Queue<Integer> q = new LinkedList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (indegree[i] == 0) {
                q.add(i);
            }
        }
        // q.add(0);
        ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
        
        while (!q.isEmpty()){
            int curr = q.poll();
            list.add(curr);
            for (int x : adj.get(curr)) {
                indegree[x]--;
                if (indegree[x] == 0) {
                    q.add(x);
                }
            }
        }
        
        if (list.size() == n) {
            for (int i : list) {
                System.out.print(i + " ");
            }
        }
        else {
            System.out.println(-1);
        }
        
        
    }
}

